<br>
With max haste we're backstabing every 5ish seconds.  At 60, with your standard Ragebringer/X setup, thats 120-1000 and change hate a backstab attempt (single minimum hit all the way to a double wiff).  Thats 120-2k+ of hate, in addition to procs and normal dps between evade attempts.  Now, with evades dropping you to a set slot in the hate list like it does, success's are, well, as usefull as intended.  Fails however really begin to hurt as the haste gets faster.<br>
<br>
I'm wondering what hidden evils would pop out if VI changed haste coding to effect all things non-casting.  Evade, sneak, hide, ID, food consumption, the works.  The only blatently obvious problem I could see is that this diminishes the monk AA rapid FD, and people would whine about that.<br>
<br>
/ooc:  Whats the roleplaying reasoning behind current haste setup?  Enhanced combat reflexes? That would still give us hasted evade attempts.  It's not &quot;overclocked&quot; or amped up metabilism, or we'd have the food consumption and such too.<br>
<br>
